nodes.text: An insurrection on Yalbec Prime took place on Yalbec Prime during the Clone Wars. The Republic sent the elite Clone Force 99—which consisted of the clones Hunter, Tech, Crosshair and Wrecker—to put down the insurrection, but part way through the mission they received communications summoning them to the planet Anaxes for their next assignment. Before they could leave the world, complications arose when Wrecker cut off the stinger of a Yalbec queen with a blade, causing a number of Yalbec males to try to mate with them. The clones eventually managed to get off Yalbec Prime and travel to Anaxes.

The insurrection was first mentioned in "The Bad Batch", an episode of the Star Wars: The Clone Wars television series. The episode was written to be part of the show's sixth season, but The Clone Wars was canceled before it was made and released. The unfinished story reels of the episodes were then shown at Celebration Anaheim in 2015, before being released on StarWars.com later that year as part of The Clone Wars Legacy. A completed version of the episode premiered on Disney+ in 2020.
